+# Requirements Quality Checklist: UC-20 View Course History
+
+**Purpose**: Validate the UC-20 requirements for completeness, clarity, consistency, measurability, and scenario coverage before task breakdown and implementation
+**Created**: 2026-03-11
+**Feature**: [spec.md](/home/thaia/ECE493Group19/specs/020-branch-course-history/spec.md)
+
+**Note**: This checklist is generated by the `/speckit.checklist` command based on feature context and requirements.
+
+## Requirement Completeness
+
+- [ ] CHK001 Are requirements defined for every student-visible course-history state: complete, partial, empty, and denied access? [Completeness, Spec §User Stories 1-3; Spec §FR-005; Spec §FR-005a; Spec §FR-006]
+- [ ] CHK002 Does the spec define what information a "course history" entry must contain beyond academic period and final outcome? [Gap, Spec §FR-002; Spec §FR-003; Spec §Key Entities]
+- [ ] CHK003 Are authorization requirements complete for both dashboard navigation and direct-link or manipulated-path access attempts? [Completeness, Spec §FR-001; Spec §FR-004; Spec §FR-006; Spec §Edge Cases]
+- [ ] CHK004 Are requirements specified for how missing or unavailable history data should be identified to the student in all partial-history cases? [Completeness, Spec §FR-005; Spec §User Story 2]
+
+## Requirement Clarity
+
+- [ ] CHK005 Is "readable format" defined with criteria that can be objectively reviewed rather than interpreted differently by different implementers? [Clarity, Ambiguity, Spec §FR-003]
+- [ ] CHK006 Is "equivalent student navigation" sufficiently specific to avoid multiple incompatible entry-point interpretations? [Clarity, Ambiguity, Spec §FR-001]
+- [ ] CHK007 Is "authorized student" defined clearly enough to distinguish self-service access from other possible academic roles or proxy access patterns? [Clarity, Spec §FR-004; Spec §Assumptions]
+- [ ] CHK008 Is "some information is missing" defined with explicit messaging or indicator requirements rather than general wording? [Clarity, Ambiguity, Spec §FR-005; Spec §SC-002]
+
+## Requirement Consistency
+
+- [ ] CHK009 Do the user stories, edge cases, and functional requirements use the same definition of course history as "all past enrollments with final outcomes" without reintroducing narrower wording? [Consistency, Spec §Clarifications; Spec §User Story 1; Spec §FR-002]
+- [ ] CHK010 Are the empty-history requirements clearly distinct from partial-history requirements everywhere the spec describes missing data conditions? [Consistency, Spec §Clarifications; Spec §Edge Cases; Spec §FR-005; Spec §FR-005a]
+- [ ] CHK011 Do the success criteria align with the functional requirements for denied access logging, rather than leaving audit expectations implied only in one section? [Consistency, Spec §FR-007; Spec §SC-003]
+
+## Acceptance Criteria Quality
+
+- [ ] CHK012 Can each success criterion be evaluated objectively without inventing additional rules during planning or implementation? [Acceptance Criteria, Measurability, Spec §SC-001 to §SC-005]
+- [ ] CHK013 Is the 30-second dashboard-to-history outcome tied to a clearly defined start point and completion point? [Clarity, Measurability, Spec §SC-004]
+- [ ] CHK014 Is "representative students" in the comprehension outcome defined well enough to avoid subjective sampling during validation? [Ambiguity, Acceptance Criteria, Spec §SC-005]
+
+## Scenario Coverage
+
+- [ ] CHK015 Are primary, alternate, and exception scenarios all covered by explicit requirements, not only by narrative user stories? [Coverage, Spec §User Stories 1-3; Spec §FR-001 to §FR-008]
+- [ ] CHK016 Are repeat-view scenarios intentionally covered as read-only behavior, including whether results must remain stable across repeated access in one session? [Coverage, Spec §Edge Cases; Spec §FR-008]
+- [ ] CHK017 Does the spec define whether unauthorized attempts against another student's history and unauthorized attempts caused by session-state mismatch are treated the same way? [Coverage, Gap, Spec §User Story 3; Spec §FR-006; Spec §FR-007]
+
+## Edge Case Coverage
+
+- [ ] CHK018 Are requirements defined for the case where course-history records exist but critical fields for display are missing or incomplete? [Edge Case, Gap, Spec §FR-005; Spec §Key Entities]
+- [ ] CHK019 Are boundary conditions defined for students with very large course histories spanning many academic periods? [Edge Case, Gap, Spec §FR-002; Plan §Scale/Scope]
+- [ ] CHK020 Does the spec distinguish "no history exists" from "history retrieval failed completely" so implementers do not collapse different states into one response? [Edge Case, Conflict, Spec §FR-005; Spec §FR-005a; Spec §Edge Cases]
+
+## Non-Functional Requirements
+
+- [ ] CHK021 Are accessibility requirements for keyboard navigation and assistive-technology announcements explicitly stated in the spec rather than only implied in the plan or contract artifacts? [Gap, Spec §Requirements; Plan §Phase 1 Design & Contracts]
+- [ ] CHK022 Are privacy expectations for course-history data exposure defined explicitly enough to guide reviewer checks beyond basic authorization wording? [Coverage, Spec §FR-004; Spec §FR-006]
+- [ ] CHK023 Are responsiveness requirements complete for both normal page loading and degraded data-availability conditions? [Completeness, Spec §SC-004; Plan §Technical Context]
+
+## Dependencies & Assumptions
+
+- [ ] CHK024 Are assumptions about existing student identity, authorization status, and academic record sources documented in a way that can be validated during planning? [Assumption, Spec §Assumptions; Spec §Dependencies]
+- [ ] CHK025 Does the spec define what happens if a dependency needed for authorization-failure logging is unavailable when access must still be denied? [Gap, Dependency, Spec §Dependencies; Spec §FR-006; Spec §FR-007]
+
+## Ambiguities & Conflicts
+
+- [ ] CHK026 Is there any conflict between "course history" as a broad record of past enrollments and possible transcript-style interpretations left elsewhere in the spec or source artifacts? [Conflict, Spec §Clarifications; Spec §FR-002]
+- [ ] CHK027 Are terms such as "course history," "final outcome," "missing," and "authorized" defined consistently enough to avoid different interpretations in tasks and acceptance evidence? [Consistency, Traceability, Spec §Clarifications; Spec §Requirements; Spec §Key Entities]
+- [ ] CHK028 Does the spec explicitly exclude out-of-scope viewer roles or editing capabilities so planners do not infer extra features? [Gap, Scope, Spec §Assumptions; Spec §FR-008]
+
+## Notes
+
+- Focus areas applied: authorization/privacy and UX/scenario coverage, with standard spec-wide review depth.
+- Intended primary user: PR reviewer.
+- This checklist tests the quality of the written requirements, not implementation behavior.
